div.div: Jumyou wo Kaitotte Moratta. Ichinen ni Tsuki, Ichimanen de.
A twenty-year-old with little hope for the future discovers a shop that buys lifespan, time, and health. This is a story dealing with the ensuing consequences. Note: Includes 2 extra chapters.

The story follows the everyday lives of Daikichi, an elderly man, and his pet cat, Tama. Daikichi has lived his entire life in a small island town, and although young people have begun moving there and the landscape and scenery have begun to change, the one thing that remains constant is Daikichi.
<i>Neko to Jiichan was a Jury Selection in the 19th Japan Media Arts Festival in 2015. The series was adapted to a live-action movie on February 22, 2019.<i>
